🎯 Interview Questions

Q: What is idempotency?
Same request multiple times → same result, no duplicate side effects.

Q: How prevent double transfer?
Using idempotency key stored with unique constraint.

Q: Where store key?
DB / Redis.

Q: Retry vs Idempotency?
Retry repeats request, idempotency prevents duplicate execution.

Q: What if two same keys hit concurrently?
Unique constraint + transaction ensures only one executes.